

## Objective

Build the football universe cleanly, with canonical data preserved, a stable SPA shell, synchronized seasonal progression, and mathematically valid continental competitions.

---

## 1) Immutable Canon Layer

These objects are locked and must never be overwritten by procedural generation:

* club names
* stadium names and capacities
* canonical player names
* canonical player clubs
* league names
* federation names
* national identities
* club rivalries

If a named player exists, he stays in his club. If a club exists, it stays in the world. If a stadium exists, its name and capacity stay fixed.

---

## 2) League Priorities

Priority domestic leagues to build and maintain first:

* Pro Liga Ishgar
* Andro League (Brislovia)
* La Liga (Javanie)
* Juba Liga (Savanna)
* Techno League (Bermudes)
* Liga No’s (Desertiqua)
* Liga One (Pays Trop Mignon)

Other nations remain compatible with the same engine and can be added later.

---

## 3) Club Strength Tiers

Use fixed strength bands so the world stays believable.

* Top club: 87–88 average OVR
* Strong club: 84–86 average OVR
* Medium club: 80–83 average OVR
* Weak club: 76–79 average OVR

Generated squads must respect the band assigned to the club.

---

## 4) Player Generation Rules

For clubs with incomplete squads:

* keep all named canonical players exactly as provided
* generate only missing players
* preserve club identity and style
* use the requested 38% local / 62% foreign mix
* do not duplicate names across clubs
* do not move a player to another club unless explicitly requested

Generated players must fit the club’s nation, league, and visual identity.

---

## 5) Season Engine Rule

All domestic leagues advance in parallel.
No league-by-league manual progression.
One season tick advances all active leagues, all ghost leagues, continental competitions, and global player stats together.

At the end of a season:

* domestic tables are finalized
* continental qualification is resolved
* awards are computed
* the next season is prepared

Every 4 seasons:

* the Euro is played

---

## 6) Champions League Equestria (CLE) — Corrected Qualification System

The CLE must reach a 36-club league phase with a mathematically clean qualification tree.

### 6.1 Direct spots

* 24 clubs qualify directly into the league phase.
* These spots go to the strongest nations / clubs by coefficient.

### 6.2 Remaining entrants

* 120 clubs enter the qualification pathway.
* They do not all start in the same round.
* Entry is staggered by coefficient.

### 6.3 Qualification path for the 120 clubs

Use four knockout rounds with coefficient-based byes.

Round 1:

* 72 clubs play
* 36 winners advance
* 48 clubs receive byes to later rounds

Round 2:

* 36 winners + 24 byes = 60 clubs
* 30 winners advance

Round 3:

* 30 winners + 6 byes = 36 clubs
* 18 winners advance

Round 4:

* 18 winners + 6 byes = 24 clubs
* 12 winners advance to the league phase

### 6.4 Final CLE league phase

* 24 direct clubs + 12 qualified clubs = 36 clubs total
* each club plays 8 different opponents
* top 8 qualify directly for the round of 16
* places 9–24 go to the playoff round
* places 25–36 are eliminated

### 6.5 Knockout phase

* playoff round: two-legged ties
* round of 16: two-legged ties
* quarterfinals: two-legged ties
* semifinals: two-legged ties
* final: single match on neutral ground
* no away-goal rule

This structure is the clean version. No fake repêchage, no mathematically forced leftovers.

---

## 7) Euro — Corrected Tournament Model

* the Euro is held every 4 seasons
* 26 players per nation are selected
* one host nation is chosen
* 24 teams participate
* 6 groups of 4 teams
* top 2 of each group advance
* the 4 best third-place teams advance
* knockout rounds are single-match elimination
* the final is a single neutral match

---

## 8) Ballon d’Or Logic

The Ballon d’Or must allow goalkeepers to win only through an exceptional season.

### Score framework by role

Attacking players:

* goals are heavily weighted
* assists are strongly weighted
* match rating is important

Midfielders:

* goals, assists, control, and influence are weighted

Defenders:

* clean sheets, tackles, interceptions, and rating are weighted

Goalkeepers:

* clean sheets, saves, save percentage, decisive moments, and trophies are weighted

### Rule

A goalkeeper may win the Ballon d’Or only if the season is truly elite, usually combined with major team success.
No role is blocked by default.
No award must be assigned through a generic average that ignores position.

---

## 9) Awards Separation Rule

Awards must be role-specific:

* best goalkeeper
* best defender
* best midfielder
* best attacker
* best young player
* top scorer
* top assist
* best overall player

A goalkeeper should not automatically rank as the best defender.
Role filters must be strict.

---

## 10) Match Engine Requirements

* use a stable scoring model
* preserve realistic goal distributions
* store events: goals, assists, minutes, ratings, man of the match
* apply positional assist coefficients
* keep match reports readable
* keep team OVR tied to the starting XI
* maintain club form across the last five matches

The engine must favor stronger clubs, but not eliminate upsets entirely.

---

## 11) SPA and Data Safety

* single-file HTML only
* vanilla JS only
* internal routing only
* localStorage persistence with versioning
* safe fallback state if stored data is broken
* visible hub on first load
* no blank screen allowed
* defensive error handling everywhere

---

## 12) Build Order

1. canonical world data
2. safe boot and visible hub
3. league views
4. clubs and squads
5. match engine
6. standings and results
7. awards
8. CLE
9. Euro
10. balancing and polish

